==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''Cupido'', from ''cupido'' desire, desire of love, from ''cupidus''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-Cupid.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
#''(Roman Mythology)'': The god of love, son of Venus; usually depicted as a naked, winged boy with bow and arrow.

